WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:04.000
Blue Moon Valley is a small village.

00:04.000 --> 00:08.000
Lee Sun lives there with her grandmother.

00:08.000 --> 00:14.000
She is very happy in Blue Moon Valley, but there's a problem.

00:14.000 --> 00:20.000
Lee Sun's grandmother is very old and very ill.

00:20.000 --> 00:27.000
She can't work anymore and has no money.

00:27.000 --> 00:32.000
One bright April morning, she says to Lee Sun,

00:32.000 --> 00:38.000
"Sit down, granddaughter. I have something to tell you."

00:38.000 --> 00:43.000
"What is it, grandmother?" asks Lee Sun.

00:43.000 --> 00:48.000
The old woman's eyes are sad and tired.

00:48.000 --> 00:52.000
"Read this letter," she says.

00:52.000 --> 00:56.000
"It's for your uncle in the big city."

00:56.000 --> 01:01.000
"I want you to go and talk to him."

01:01.000 --> 01:09.000
Lee Sun reads the letter, then looks at her grandmother.

01:09.000 --> 01:14.000
"You're asking him to give me a job in his circus?"

01:14.000 --> 01:19.000
"Yes," the old woman answers.

01:19.000 --> 01:24.000
Lee Sun and her grandmother talk for a long time.

01:24.000 --> 01:28.000
Lee Sun doesn't want to leave Blue Moon Valley.

01:28.000 --> 01:32.000
"It's my home," she says.

01:32.000 --> 01:36.000
"But every child leaves home one day,"

01:36.000 --> 01:39.000
the old woman answers.

01:39.000 --> 01:42.000
"And you're not a child now."

01:42.000 --> 01:48.000
"You're a young woman. I want you to be free."

01:49.000 --> 01:53.000
In the end, Lee Sun looks at the floor and says,

01:53.000 --> 01:57.000
"Yes, grandmother."

01:57.000 --> 02:02.000
Two days later, she leaves the village.

02:02.000 --> 02:07.000
In the next week, Lee Sun walks a long way.

02:07.000 --> 02:13.000
She sees mountains, fields, trees and farms.

02:13.000 --> 02:18.000
Every morning, she drinks from cold rivers.

02:18.000 --> 02:26.000
Every night, she sleeps under thousands of bright stars.

02:26.000 --> 02:31.000
Then, after eight days, she comes to the big city.

02:31.000 --> 02:36.000
It has high walls with stone lions on top of them.

02:36.000 --> 02:42.000
Hundreds of people are running left and right in front of her.

02:42.000 --> 02:46.000
"Excuse me," she says to an old man.

02:46.000 --> 02:49.000
"Do you know this address?"

02:49.000 --> 02:53.000
She shows him her grandmother's letter.

02:53.000 --> 02:56.000
"You want the circus?"

02:56.000 --> 02:59.000
he says. "That's easy."

02:59.000 --> 03:09.000
"Go down this street and turn left at the end."

03:09.000 --> 03:14.000
Ten minutes later, Lee Sun is at the circus.

03:14.000 --> 03:17.000
Her uncle is very happy to see her.

03:17.000 --> 03:21.000
"Oh, yes, of course you can have a job."

03:21.000 --> 03:26.000
He says, "Come with me."

03:26.000 --> 03:30.000
Behind the circus, there are some big cages.

03:30.000 --> 03:34.000
"Here we are," says Lee Sun's uncle.

03:34.000 --> 03:39.000
"You can help to wash the animals," he smiles.

03:39.000 --> 03:43.000
"And you can help to give them their food too."

03:43.000 --> 03:46.000
"Do you understand?"

03:46.000 --> 03:49.000
Lee Sun looks at all the animals.

03:49.000 --> 03:56.000
There are monkeys, tigers, elephants, horses and lions.

03:56.000 --> 03:59.000
Then she looks at her uncle again.

03:59.000 --> 04:04.000
"Yes, uncle," she says.

04:04.000 --> 04:09.000
Lee Sun works very hard for three months.

04:09.000 --> 04:14.000
Every week, she writes to her grandmother.

04:14.000 --> 04:23.000
In her letters, she says, "I'm very happy," but she's not.

04:23.000 --> 04:28.000
She tells her only friend, Choo Choo, the panda.

04:28.000 --> 04:31.000
"I want to go home."

04:31.000 --> 04:37.000
Then one day, her uncle says, "The emperor's coming here tomorrow."

04:37.000 --> 04:42.000
"I want all the animals to be very, very clean."

04:42.000 --> 04:44.000
"All right?"

04:44.000 --> 04:49.000
"Of course," says Lee Sun.

04:49.000 --> 04:55.000
The next morning, Lee Sun is giving the tigers their food.

04:55.000 --> 05:03.000
Suddenly, she hears her uncle say, "You've got another job?"

05:03.000 --> 05:07.000
She opens the long red curtains.

05:07.000 --> 05:11.000
Her uncle's talking to Yume.

05:11.000 --> 05:16.000
She works with Wu Chi, the horseman.

05:16.000 --> 05:19.000
"Yes," says Yume.

05:19.000 --> 05:22.000
"And I'm leaving today."

05:22.000 --> 05:26.000
"Goodbye."

05:26.000 --> 05:32.000
After she leaves, Lee Sun's uncle looks at Wu Chi.

05:32.000 --> 05:36.000
"Oh, now what can we do?"

05:36.000 --> 05:40.000
he asks.

05:40.000 --> 05:45.000
A moment later, he sees Lee Sun.

05:45.000 --> 05:51.000
"Of course," he says. "Lee Sun."

05:51.000 --> 05:54.000
"She can help you this evening."

05:54.000 --> 05:56.000
"What?"

05:56.000 --> 05:59.000
Wu Chi laughs.

05:59.000 --> 06:04.000
"But she can't learn Yume's job in one day."

06:04.000 --> 06:07.000
"Do you have another answer?"

06:07.000 --> 06:11.000
asks Lee Sun's uncle.

06:11.000 --> 06:15.000
Wu Chi says nothing.

06:15.000 --> 06:22.000
In ten minutes, Lee Sun is wearing Yume's circus clothes.

06:22.000 --> 06:27.000
That evening, the emperor arrives at seven o'clock.

06:27.000 --> 06:31.000
He's wearing beautiful gold clothes.

06:31.000 --> 06:36.000
He sits down and watches the circus.

06:36.000 --> 06:42.000
Then, at the end, he talks to Lee Sun's uncle.

06:42.000 --> 06:47.000
"Who's that new girl with your horseman?"

06:47.000 --> 06:50.000
he asks.

06:50.000 --> 06:53.000
"Her name is Lee Sun,"

06:53.000 --> 06:55.000
comes the answer.

06:55.000 --> 06:58.000
The emperor smiles.

06:58.000 --> 07:03.000
"She's young, but very good."

07:03.000 --> 07:07.000
"Oh, thank you, emperor,"

07:07.000 --> 07:11.000
says Lee Sun's uncle.

07:11.000 --> 07:17.000
After that evening, Lee Sun doesn't clean the animals' cages anymore.

07:17.000 --> 07:22.000
She works with Wu Chi every day.

07:22.000 --> 07:25.000
But that's not all.

07:25.000 --> 07:29.000
She starts to love the horseman too.

07:29.000 --> 07:36.000
They often walk in a beautiful park next to the emperor's palace.

07:36.000 --> 07:47.000
There, one day in October, Wu Chi puts a hand on Lee Sun's arm.

07:47.000 --> 07:53.000
"You make me very happy," he says.

07:53.000 --> 07:57.000
"I want you to be my wife."

07:57.000 --> 08:01.000
Lee Sun doesn't know what to say.

08:01.000 --> 08:09.000
She wants to be Wu Chi's wife, but not here in the big city.

08:09.000 --> 08:15.000
She wants to live with him at home in Blue Moon Valley.

08:15.000 --> 08:20.000
She tells him this and looks into his eyes.

08:20.000 --> 08:23.000
"Can you understand?"

08:23.000 --> 08:25.000
she asks.

08:25.000 --> 08:28.000
Wu Chi looks down.

08:28.000 --> 08:32.000
"I don't know," he answers.

08:32.000 --> 08:36.000
"My home's here in the city."

08:36.000 --> 08:39.000
"Let me think about it."

08:39.000 --> 08:43.000
"We can talk again tomorrow."

08:43.000 --> 08:47.000
It's a very long night for Lee Sun.

08:47.000 --> 08:50.000
She cannot sleep.

08:50.000 --> 08:55.000
She goes to see her old friend, Choo Choo.

08:55.000 --> 09:00.000
"Oh, what's he going to say tomorrow?"

09:00.000 --> 09:03.000
she asks the panda.

09:03.000 --> 09:06.000
"Am I doing the right thing?"

09:06.000 --> 09:11.000
"I love him, but I can't live in the city."

09:11.000 --> 09:14.000
"I don't like it."

09:14.000 --> 09:19.000
"My home's back in Blue Moon Valley."

09:20.000 --> 09:23.000
Choo Choo looks at Lee Sun.

09:23.000 --> 09:29.000
His eyes are big, brown and sad.

09:29.000 --> 09:37.000
Early next morning, Wu Chi finds Lee Sun in the panda's cage.

09:37.000 --> 09:41.000
"Come with me," he says.

09:41.000 --> 09:45.000
They go to see Lee Sun's uncle.

09:45.000 --> 09:51.000
Wu Chi has something to tell him.

09:51.000 --> 09:56.000
"Lee Sun's going to be my wife," he says.

09:56.000 --> 09:59.000
"But that's not all."

09:59.000 --> 10:02.000
"We are leaving the circus."

10:02.000 --> 10:08.000
"I'm going to be a farmer in Blue Moon Valley."

10:08.000 --> 10:14.000
"Oh, Wu Chi," says Lee Sun.

10:14.000 --> 10:18.000
She is very, very happy.

10:18.000 --> 10:25.000
One week later, Lee Sun and Wu Chi leave the city.

10:25.000 --> 10:29.000
Everyone comes to say goodbye.

10:29.000 --> 10:35.000
Then, at the last minute, four men arrive.

10:35.000 --> 10:39.000
They're carrying a big box.

10:39.000 --> 10:41.000
"What's this?"

10:41.000 --> 10:44.000
asks Lee Sun.

10:44.000 --> 10:50.000
"It's something from all of us," says her uncle.

10:50.000 --> 10:54.000
"Please open it."

10:54.000 --> 10:57.000
Lee Sun opens the box.

10:57.000 --> 11:02.000
"Oh, Choo Choo," she says.

11:02.000 --> 11:06.000
"Oh, uncle, thank you."

11:06.000 --> 11:09.000
"Thank you."
